<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><HierarchySearchSerializer xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><a name="SCPI"><d><e>abort</e><e>abort</e><e>aborts a measurement in progress.</e></d><d><e>calculate:average:all</e><e>all</e><e>the query returns the arithmetic mean (average), standard deviation, minimum value and maximum value of all measurements taken since the last time statistics were cleared. </e></d><d><e>calculate:average:average</e><e>average</e><e>the query returns the arithmetic mean (average) of all measurements taken since the last time statistics were cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:average:clear:immediate</e><e>immediate</e><e>the command clears all computed statistics: minimum, maximum, average, peak-to-peak, count and standard deviation. </e></d><d><e>calculate:average:count</e><e>count</e><e>the query returns the count of all measurements taken since the last time statistics were cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:average:maximum</e><e>maximum</e><e>the query returns the maximum value of all measurements taken since the last time statistics were cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:average:minimum</e><e>minimum</e><e>the query returns the minimum value of all measurements taken since the last time statistics were cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:average:ptpeak</e><e>ptpeak</e><e>the query returns the peak to peak value of all measurements taken since the last time statistics were cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:average:sdeviation</e><e>sdeviation</e><e>the query returns the standard deviation of all measurements taken since the last time statistics were cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:average:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables statistics computation.
</e></d><d><e>calculate:clear:immediate</e><e>immediate</e><e>this command clears all limits, histogram data, statistics, and measurements.</e></d><d><e>calculate:limit:clear:immediate</e><e>immediate</e><e>the command clears front panel indications of limits being exceeded and clears bit 11 ("lower limit failed") and bit 12 ("upper limit failed") in the condition register of the questionable data register event register group.</e></d><d><e>calculate:limit:lower:data</e><e>data</e><e>the command sets the lower limit.
the query returns the lower limit.


</e></d><d><e>calculate:limit:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables limit testing.
the query returns the limit testing state.
</e></d><d><e>calculate:limit:upper:data</e><e>data</e><e>the command sets an upper limit.
the query returns an upper limit.


</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:db:reference</e><e>reference</e><e>the command stores a relative value in the multimeter's db relative register.</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:dbm:reference</e><e>reference</e><e>the command selects the reference resistance for converting voltage measurements to dbm. </e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:function</e><e>function</e><e>the command selects the operation performed by the scaling function.
the query returns the operation performed by the scaling function.</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:gain</e><e>gain</e><e>the command stores a gain value m for the scaling function.
</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:offset</e><e>offset</e><e>the command stores an offset value b for the scaling function.</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:reference</e><e>reference</e><e>the command stores a reference value for the pct function.</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:reference:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command enables or disables automatic reference selection for the db scaling functions.
the query returns the automatic reference selection state for the db scaling functions.</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables the scaling function.
the query returns the scaling function state.</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:unit</e><e>unit</e><e>the command allows you to specify the custom label of up to four characters (for example, rpm or °c) for scaled measurements.</e></d><d><e>calculate:scale:unit:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables displaying the unit  string with measurements on the front panel when the scaling function  is enabled.</e></d><d><e>calculate:smoothing:response</e><e>response</e><e>the command selects the number of measurements to be averaged by the moving average (boxcar) filter.</e></d><d><e>calculate:smoothing:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables a smoothing (moving  average) filter on the measurements. </e></d><d><e>calculate:tchart:state</e><e>state</e><e>this command enables or disables trend chart data when controlling the instrument from remote.</e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:all</e><e>all</e><e>the query returns a comma-separated list of the lower and upper range values, the number of measurements, and the bin data collected since the last time the histogram data was cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:clear:immediate</e><e>immediate</e><e>the command clears the histogram data and restarts histogram ranging if it is enabled. </e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:count</e><e>count</e><e>the query returns the number of measurements collected since the last time the histogram was cleared.</e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:data</e><e>data</e><e>the query returns the bin data.</e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:points</e><e>points</e><e>the command sets the number of bins between the lower and upper range values for the histogram. </e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:range:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command enables or disables automatic selection of the histogram's lower and upper range values.

</e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:range:lower</e><e>lower</e><e>the command sets the lower range value for the histogram.
the query returns the lower range value for the histogram.</e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:range:upper</e><e>upper</e><e>the command sets the upper range value for the histogram.
the query returns the upper range value for the histogram.</e></d><d><e>calculate:transform:histogram:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables histogram computation.
the query returns the histogram computation state.</e></d><d><e>calibration:adc</e><e>adc</e><e>the query performs a low-level calibration of the adc (analog-to-digital converter) circuitry.</e></d><d><e>calibration:all</e><e>all</e><e>the query performs a calibration using the calibration value based on the function and range.</e></d><d><e>calibration:count</e><e>count</e><e>the query returns the calibration count.</e></d><d><e>calibration:date</e><e>date</e><e>the query returns the date of the last calibration in the format yyyy,mm,dd. </e></d><d><e>calibration:secure:code</e><e>code</e><e>the command sets the security code to prevent unauthorized calibrations.</e></d><d><e>calibration:secure:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command unsecures or secures the instrument for calibration.
the query returns the secure state.</e></d><d><e>calibration:store</e><e>store</e><e>the command takes calibration constants in volatile memory (calibration:all?), and places them in nonvolatile memory, where they are not changed by cycling power, *rst, or system:preset.</e></d><d><e>calibration:string</e><e>string</e><e>the command stores a message in calibration memory.</e></d><d><e>calibration:temperature</e><e>temperature</e><e>the query returns the temperature of the last calibration in °c. </e></d><d><e>calibration:time</e><e>time</e><e>the query returns the amount of time since the last calibration in the format  hh,mm,ss.sss. </e></d><d><e>calibration:value</e><e>value</e><e>the command specifies the value of the known calibration signal.
the query returns the value of the known calibration signal.</e></d><d><e>configure</e><e>configure</e><e>the query returns a quoted string indicating the present function, range, and resolution. </e></d><d><e>configure:capacitance</e><e>capacitance</e><e>the command sets all measurement and trigger parameters to their default values for capacitance measurements. also specifies the range.</e></d><d><e>configure:continuity</e><e>continuity</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for continuity measurements.</e></d><d><e>configure:current:ac</e><e>ac</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for ac current measurements. also specifies the range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:current:dc</e><e>dc</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for dc current measurements. also specifies the range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:diode</e><e>diode</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for diode tests.

</e></d><d><e>configure:frequency</e><e>frequency</e><e>the command sets all measurement and trigger parameters to their default values for frequency measurements. also specifies the frequency range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:fresistance</e><e>fresistance</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for 4-wire (fresistance)resistance measurements. also specifies the range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:period</e><e>period</e><e>the command sets all measurement and trigger parameters to their default values for period measurements. also specifies the period range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:resistance</e><e>resistance</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for 2-wire (resistance) resistance measurements. also specifies the range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:temperature</e><e>temperature</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for temperature measurements. also specifies the transducer and the measurement resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:voltage:ac</e><e>ac</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for ac voltage measurements. also specifies the range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:voltage:dc</e><e>dc</e><e>the command sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for dc voltage measurements. also specifies the range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>configure:voltage:dc:ratio</e><e>ratio</e><e>the command sets all measurement and trigger parameters to their default values for dc voltage to dc voltage ratio measurements. also specifies the range and resolution.</e></d><d><e>data:last</e><e>last</e><e>the query returns the last measurement taken.</e></d><d><e>data:points</e><e>points</e><e>the query returns the total number of measurements currently in reading memory.</e></d><d><e>data:points:event:threshold</e><e>threshold</e><e>the command sets the number of measurements to store in reading memory before setting bit 9 in the standard operation register group event register to 1.</e></d><d><e>data:remove</e><e>remove</e><e>the query reads and erases &lt;num_readings&gt; measurements from the reading memory.</e></d><d><e>display:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command disables or enables the front-panel display. 
the query returns the front-panel display state.</e></d><d><e>display:text:clear</e><e>clear</e><e>the command clears the text message from the display.</e></d><d><e>display:text:data</e><e>data</e><e>the command displays a text message on the front-panel display. </e></d><d><e>display:view</e><e>view</e><e>the command specifies whether measurement data is displayed in numeric, histogram, trend chart, or bar meter form.</e></d><d><e>fetch</e><e>fetch</e><e>the query waits for measurements to complete and copies all available measurements to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>format:border</e><e>border</e><e>the command used for binary block transfers only. selects the byte order for binary block transfers using measure?, read?, fetch?, data:remove? and r?.</e></d><d><e>format:data</e><e>data</e><e>the command specifies the data format to be either ascii or real.
the query returns the data format.</e></d><d><e>hcopy:sdump:data</e><e>data</e><e>the query returns the front panel display image ("screen shot").</e></d><d><e>hcopy:sdump:data:format</e><e>format</e><e>the command specifies the image format.</e></d><d><e>initiate:immediate</e><e>immediate</e><e>the command changes the state of the triggering system from "idle" to "wait-for-trigger", and clears the previous set of measurements from reading memory.</e></d><d><e>lxi:identify:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command shows or removes the lxi web identify indicator on the display.</e></d><d><e>lxi:mdns:enable</e><e>enable</e><e>the command disables or enables the multicast domain name system (mdns), which provides the capabilities of a dns server for service discovery in a small network without a dns server.</e></d><d><e>lxi:mdns:hname:resolved</e><e>resolved</e><e>the query returns the resolved (unique) mdns hostname.</e></d><d><e>lxi:mdns:sname:desired</e><e>desired</e><e>the command sets the desired mdns service name.</e></d><d><e>lxi:mdns:sname:resolved</e><e>resolved</e><e>the query returns the resolved mdns service name.</e></d><d><e>lxi:reset</e><e>reset</e><e>the command resets lan settings to a known operating state, beginning with dhcp, and clears the web interface password.</e></d><d><e>lxi:restart</e><e>restart</e><e>the command restarts the lan with the current settings.</e></d><d><e>measure:capacitance</e><e>capacitance</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for capacitance measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:continuity</e><e>continuity</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for continuity test and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:current:ac</e><e>ac</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for ac current measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:current:dc</e><e>dc</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for dc current measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:diode</e><e>diode</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for diode test measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:frequency</e><e>frequency</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for frequency measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:fresistance</e><e>fresistance</e><e>the query sets all measurement and trigger parameters to their default values for 4-wire resistance (fresistance) measurements, and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:period</e><e>period</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for period measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:resistance</e><e>resistance</e><e>the query sets all measurement and trigger parameters to their default values for 2-wire (resistance) measurements, and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:temperature</e><e>temperature</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for temperature measurements, then immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:voltage:ac</e><e>ac</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for ac voltage measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:voltage:dc</e><e>dc</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for dc voltage measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>measure:voltage:dc:ratio</e><e>ratio</e><e>the query sets all measurement parameters and trigger parameters to their default values for dc voltage ratio measurements and immediately triggers a measurement. the results are sent directly to the instrument's output buffer.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:catalog:all</e><e>all</e><e>the query returns a list of files in the specified folder.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:cdirectory</e><e>cdirectory</e><e>the command selects the default folder for mmemory subsystem commands.
the query returns the current default folder.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:copy</e><e>copy</e><e>the command copies &lt;file1&gt; to &lt;file2&gt;. each file name must include the file extension.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:delete</e><e>delete</e><e>the command deletes a file. </e></d><d><e>mmemory:download:data</e><e>data</e><e>the command downloads data from the host computer to a file whose name has been specified by mmemory:download:fname.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:download:fname</e><e>fname</e><e>the command creates or opens the specified filename prior to writing data to that file with mmemory:download:data.

</e></d><d><e>mmemory:format:reading:cseparator</e><e>cseparator</e><e>the command specifies the character used to separate the columns in stored data.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:format:reading:information</e><e>information</e><e>the command disables/enables header information and reading numbers in stored data.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:format:reading:rlimit</e><e>rlimit</e><e>the command when enabled, limits the maximum number rows per stored .csv data file to one million, including any header row, if enabled.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:load:preferences</e><e>preferences</e><e>the command reboots the instrument and loads the nonvolatile i/o settings and user preferences from a file.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:load:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command loads an instrument state from a state file.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:mdirectory</e><e>mdirectory</e><e>the command makes a new directory (folder) on the mass storage medium.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:move</e><e>move</e><e>the command moves and/or renames &lt;file1&gt; to &lt;file2&gt;. each file name must include the file extension.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:rdirectory</e><e>rdirectory</e><e>the command removes a directory (folder) on the mass storage medium.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:state:recall:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command disables or enables the automatic recall of a specific stored instrument state at power-on.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:state:recall:select</e><e>select</e><e>the command selects which instrument state will be used at power-on if the automatic recall mode is enabled .</e></d><d><e>mmemory:state:valid</e><e>valid</e><e>the query returns 1 if the specified state file exists and contains a valid state file.returns 0 otherwise.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:store:data</e><e>data</e><e>the command stores all measurements in reading memory to the specified data file. </e></d><d><e>mmemory:store:preferences</e><e>preferences</e><e>the command stores nonvolatile i/o settings and user preferences to a file. </e></d><d><e>mmemory:store:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command saves the current instrument state to a state file.</e></d><d><e>mmemory:upload</e><e>upload</e><e>the query uploads the contents of a file from the instrument to the host computer.</e></d><d><e>output:trigger:slope</e><e>slope</e><e>the command selects the slope of the voltmeter complete output signal on the rear-panel vm comp bnc connector.</e></d><d><e>r</e><e>r</e><e>the query reads and erases all available measurements from the reading memory up to the specified &lt;max_readings&gt;. </e></d><d><e>read</e><e>read</e><e>the query starts a new sets of measurements, waits for all measurements to complete, and transfers all available measurements. </e></d><d><e>route:terminals</e><e>terminals</e><e>the query indicates which input terminals are selected on the 34461a front panel front/rear switch.</e></d><d><e>sample:count</e><e>count</e><e>the command specifies the number of measurements (samples) the instrument takes per trigger.</e></d><d><e>sample:count:pretrigger</e><e>pretrigger</e><e>the command allows collection of the data being digitized before  the trigger. reserves memory for pretrigger  samples up to the specified number of pretrigger samples.</e></d><d><e>sample:source</e><e>source</e><e>the command determines sample timing.</e></d><d><e>sample:timer</e><e>timer</e><e>the command sets a sample interval for timed sampling (sample:source timer) when the sample count is greater than one. </e></d><d><e>sense:capacitance:null:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command turns the null function on or off for capacitance measurements.
the query returns the null function state for capacitance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:capacitance:null:value</e><e>value</e><e>the command stores a null value for capacitance measurements.
the query returns a null value for capacitance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:capacitance:null:value:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command enables or disables automatic null value selection for capacitance measurements.
the query returns automatic null value selection state for capacitance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:capacitance:range</e><e>range</e><e>the command selects a fixed  range for capacitance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:capacitance:range:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command disables or enables autoranging for capacitance measurements.
the query returns the autoranging for capacitance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:capacitance:secondary</e><e>secondary</e><e>the command selects the secondary measurement function for capacitance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:bandwidth</e><e>bandwidth</e><e>the command sets the bandwidth for ac current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:null:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables the null function for ac current measurements.
the query returns the null function state for ac current measurements.

</e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:null:value</e><e>value</e><e>the command sets the null value for ac current measurements.
the query returns the null value for ac current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:null:value:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command enables or disables automatic null value selection for ac current measurements.
the query returns the automatic null value selection state for ac current measurements.

</e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:range</e><e>range</e><e>the command selects a fixed measurement range for ac current measurements on the 3 a terminals.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:range:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command disables or enables autoranging for ac current measurements. 
the query returns the autoranging state for ac current measurements. </e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:secondary</e><e>secondary</e><e>the command selects the secondary measurement function for ac current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:ac:terminals</e><e>terminals</e><e>the command configures the ac current measurement to measure the source on the 3 a or 10 a terminals.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:aperture</e><e>aperture</e><e>the command specifies  the integration time in seconds  (called aperture time) for dc current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:aperture:enabled</e><e>enabled</e><e>the command enables the setting of integration time in seconds  (called aperture time) for  dc current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:nplcycles</e><e>nplcycles</e><e>the command sets the integration time in number of power line cycles (plc) for dc current measurements. </e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:null:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables the null function for dc current measurements.

</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:null:value</e><e>value</e><e>the command sets the null value for dc current measurements.

</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:null:value:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command enables or disables automatic null value selection for dc current measurements.

</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:range</e><e>range</e><e>the command selects a fixed measurement range for dc current measurements on the 3 a terminals. </e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:range:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command disables or enables autoranging for dc current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:resolution</e><e>resolution</e><e>the command selects the measurement resolution for dc current measurements. </e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:secondary</e><e>secondary</e><e>the command selects the secondary measurement function for dc current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:terminals</e><e>terminals</e><e>the command configures the dc current measurement to measure the source on the 3 a or 10 a terminals.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:dc:zero:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command disables or enables the autozero mode for dc current measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:current:switch:mode</e><e>mode</e><e>the command selects the fast or continuous range change mode for ac and dc current measurements. </e></d><d><e>sense:data2</e><e>data2</e><e>the query retrieves the secondary measurement.</e></d><d><e>sense:data2:clear:immediate</e><e>immediate</e><e>the command clears the latest result(s) of the secondary measurement.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:aperture</e><e>aperture</e><e>the command sets the aperture time (gate time) for frequency measurements.
the query returns the aperture time (gate time) for frequency measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:null:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables the null function for frequency measurements.
the query returns the null function state for frequency measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:null:value</e><e>value</e><e>the command stores a null value for frequency measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:null:value:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command enables or disables automatic null value selection for frequency and period measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:range:lower</e><e>lower</e><e>the command sets the ac bandwidth used to detect the signal during frequency measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:secondary</e><e>secondary</e><e>the command selects the secondary measurement function for frequency measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:timeout:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command controls how long the instrument waits before timing out on a frequency measurement when no signal is present.</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:voltage:range</e><e>range</e><e>the command selects a fixed voltage range for frequency measurements.

</e></d><d><e>sense:frequency:voltage:range:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command disables or enables voltage autoranging for frequency measurements. 
the query returns the voltage autoranging state for frequency measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:fresistance:aperture</e><e>aperture</e><e>the command specifies the integration time in seconds (called aperture time) for resistance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:fresistance:aperture:enabled</e><e>enabled</e><e>the command enables the setting of integration time in seconds (called aperture time) for resistance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:fresistance:nplcycles</e><e>nplcycles</e><e>the command sets the integration time in number of power line cycles (plc) for all resistance measurements. </e></d><d><e>sense:fresistance:null:state</e><e>state</e><e>the command enables or disables the null function for all resistance measurements.
the query returns the null function state for all resistance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:fresistance:null:value</e><e>value</e><e>the command stores a null value for all resistance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:fresistance:null:value:auto</e><e>auto</e><e>the command enables or disables automatic null value selection for all resistance measurements.</e></d><d><e>sense:fresistance:ocompensated</e><e>ocompensated</e><e>the command enables or disables offset compensation.
